These should be very helpful in preventing hospitalization/death.

Now is the time to sort out distribution, eligibility criteria etc so we're not caught flat-footed when they are approved/arrive.

They all matter, but contextualizing them is what's most important.

(If you are in Canada, keep an eye on ICU-related metrics as this is one of the major bottlenecks in our healthcare system)
